iDN42, aka Decentralized Network 42, is a large, decentralized		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iVPN-based network.
But unlike other traditional VPNs, DN42 itself		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
idoesn't provide any VPN exits,
which means it doesn't allow you to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ibypass Internet censorships or unlock
streaming services. On the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icontrary, the goal of DN42 is to simulate another
Internet. It uses		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imuch of the technology running on modern Internet backbones
(BGP,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
irecursive DNS, etc), and is a great replica of a real network		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ienvironment.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iIn short, DN42 is:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- NOT suitable for users only seeking privacy protection or bypassing		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icensorship		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- NOT suitable for users consuming large amounts of bandwidth/data,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
isuch as for
unlocking streaming services		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- IS suitable for users learning about networking, practicing		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iconfiguration of
servers and routers, and even preparing for an AS on		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ithe real Internet		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- IS suitable for users with a real AS, but is worried of		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
hknocking out the Internet due to configuration errors	URL:https://blog.cloudflare.com/how-verizon-and-a-bgp-optimizer-knocked-large-parts-of-the-internet-offline-today/	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i,
and want a test field.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iBecause of this, the bar to enter DN42 is a bit high. Just like the		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ireal
Internet, you will be playing the role of a ISP, register your		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ipersonal ID, ASN,
IPv4 and IPv6 blocks, and announce your IP blocks on		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iyour server with BGP. You
also need to contact other users and peer		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwith them, so you can enter the "real"
DN42 step by step.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iDN42 is running on `172.20.0.0/14` and `fd00::/8`, IP blocks reserved		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifor
internal usage. In other words, whatever you do on DN42 won't		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iimpact real
Interner connections.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
