iSkill Requirements		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iThis post assumes that you are already capable of:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- You have a Linux environment (either dual-boot/virtual machine/VPS		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iis fine).		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- You know how to use common Linux commands (`cd`, `ls`, etc), how to		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iinstall
packages on your Linux OS (`apt`, `yum`, etc.), and how to use		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iat least one
editor (either graphical editors like `gedit` or		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`vscode`, or command-line
ones like `vim` or `nano`). If you don't		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iknow how to do this, please have a
look at		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
hthis guide	URL:https://ryanstutorials.net/linuxtutorial/	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- You know basic usage of Git version control system, like		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ipush/pull/commit. If
you don't, please have a look at		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
hthis guide	URL:https://guides.github.com/introduction/git-handbook/	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- You have a moderate level of knowledge in networking, know what IP		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iand MAC
addresses are, know the working principles of switches and		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
irouters, can do
basic networking diagnosis under Linux (with `ping`,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i`traceroute`, etc.),
have heard of dynamic routing protocols like BGP		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ior OSPF. If you don't,
please have a look at		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
hthis guide (Chapter 1-8)	URL:https://www.cs.unh.edu/cnrg/people/gherrin/linux-net.html	{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iIf you don't fulfill the knowledge required, it's very likely that you		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icannot
understand important aspects in this guide, make mistakes		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iduring the
configuration process, and cause trouble to other users in		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iDN42.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
