i- Cons:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Difficult to configure, may need repeated communication/discussions		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Or simply use plain GRE:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Pro:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Available on hardware routers		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Easy to configure		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Cons:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iNO ENCRYPTION! PLAINTEXT TRANSMISSION!		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iNO ENCRYPTION! PLAINTEXT TRANSMISSION!		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iNO ENCRYPTION! PLAINTEXT TRANSMISSION!		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- On Linux servers, you may also use ZeroTier One for internal		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iconnections or
for peering.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Pros:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- Nice web interface		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
